{"word":"μιμητής","slug":"μιμητής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μιμητής</b></el> <el>(μῑμητής, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μιμέομαι'><el>μιμέομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>an imitator, copyist</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>one who represents</i> characters, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a mere actor, an impostor</i> (<a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ὑποκριτής</el>), <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}